---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FaqAccordion from '../../components/FaqAccordion.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
import { faqPageSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is answer engine optimization?',
    answer:
      "Answer engine optimization (AEO) is the practice of structuring content so AI systems — ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Google's AI Overviews — can find it, understand it, and cite it as a direct answer. Where traditional SEO optimizes for ranking in a list of links, AEO optimizes for being the source an AI system pulls from to construct its answer.",
  },
  {
    question: 'How is AEO different from SEO?',
    answer:
      'SEO targets a ranking position on a search results page; the user still has to click through to get an answer. AEO targets being the cited or quoted source inside an AI-generated answer, where the user may never visit your site at all. The two share infrastructure — crawlable pages, clear structure, authoritative content — but the success metric is different: rank versus citation.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which AI platforms does AEO target?',
    answer:
      "The primary platforms are ChatGPT, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and Claude. Each has a different retrieval and crawling approach, but all reward the same underlying qualities: clear definitions, well-structured pages, and content that directly answers a specific question rather than circling it.",
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I get my brand to appear in ChatGPT and Perplexity?',
    answer:
      "Appearing in ChatGPT and Perplexity responses depends on your content being crawlable (static HTML, not JavaScript-only rendering), structured around clear questions and definitions, and credible enough to be treated as a reliable source. There is no submission process — visibility comes from being genuinely citable, not from technical tricks.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need AEO if I already invest in SEO?',
    answer:
      "Yes. SEO and AEO overlap but are not interchangeable. A page can rank well in traditional search while being invisible to AI answer engines if it lacks clear definitional structure, or it can be highly citable by AI systems while ranking modestly in traditional search. Brands that only optimize for one are leaving visibility on the table in the other.",
  },
  {
    question: 'How long does AEO take to show results?',
    answer:
      "AEO citation can happen faster than traditional ranking growth, since AI systems re-crawl and re-evaluate sources more frequently than Google's index updates for competitive keywords. That said, building the authority that makes a source trustworthy enough to cite consistently is still a multi-month effort, not an overnight one.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Answer Engine Optimization Services | Schwartz Marketing Lab"
  description="Answer engine optimization services that help B2B brands appear in ChatGPT, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and traditional search."
  canonicalPath="/services/answer-engine-optimization"
  schema={faqPageSchema(faqs)}
>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <span class="eyebrow">Answer Engine Optimization</span>
      <h1>Answer Engine Optimization That Drives Revenue</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        AI search is no longer experimental — it's where a growing share of B2B buyers start their research. We help
        brands earn visibility inside ChatGPT, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and Claude, not just on page one of
        Google.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="button" href="/packages">See how we work with clients</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>What Is Answer Engine Optimization?</h2>
      <p>
        Answer engine optimization (AEO) is the discipline of structuring content so AI systems can retrieve it,
        understand it, and use it to construct an answer — with or without sending a click to your site. It treats
        ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Google's AI Overviews as discovery surfaces in their own right, not as
        an extension of the traditional search results page.
      </p>
      <p>
        Practically, this means writing content that answers a specific question clearly and early, naming the
        entities and platforms involved explicitly, and making sure the page is structured in a way a retrieval
        system can parse — not buried under animation, infinite scroll, or JavaScript-rendered text that crawlers
        never see.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Why AEO Matters for B2B Brands</h2>
      <p>
        B2B buyers increasingly use AI tools to shortlist vendors, compare categories, and validate claims before
        they ever fill out a contact form. If your brand isn't part of the answer an AI system gives when a
        prospect asks "what is the best approach to X" or "who does Y," you've lost the opportunity before the
        prospect reaches your website.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is especially true for categories that are still forming. Being the source AI systems cite for a
        definition — rather than competing for attention after the category is already crowded — is a compounding
        advantage that gets harder to win later.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>AEO vs. SEO: What's Actually Different</h2>
      <p>
        SEO and AEO share infrastructure: both reward crawlable pages, clear writing, and earned authority. They
        diverge in what counts as success. SEO succeeds when your page ranks and earns a click. AEO succeeds when
        an AI system treats your content as a trustworthy source and surfaces it — sometimes with a citation,
        sometimes without a click at all.
      </p>
      <p>
        That distinction changes how a page should be written. Strong AEO content front-loads a direct, quotable
        answer instead of building up to one, and it names things explicitly — platforms, competitors, categories —
        because AI systems match on entities, not just keywords.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Where We Help You Appear</h2>
      <p>
        We work across the platforms B2B buyers actually use for research: ChatGPT, Google AI Overviews,
        Perplexity, and Claude. Each platform retrieves and weighs sources differently, but all of them favor
        content that is structurally clear, directly responsive to a question, and backed by demonstrable
        expertise rather than marketing language.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How We Approach AEO</h2>
      <p>
        Our process starts with identifying the exact questions your buyers are asking AI systems — not just the
        keywords they'd type into Google — and auditing whether your current content can actually be retrieved and
        understood by those systems. Many sites fail at this step before content quality is even a factor:
        JavaScript-rendered text, missing structured data, and buried definitions are invisible to AI crawlers no
        matter how good the writing is underneath.
      </p>
      <p>
        From there, we build content structured around clear definitions, comparison frameworks, and FAQ sections
        marked up with schema — the same structural signals that make a page easy for a human to scan also make it
        easy for a retrieval system to extract.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>What an AEO Engagement Includes</h2>
      <p>
        A typical engagement includes a technical and content audit of your existing site's AI visibility, a
        prioritized list of definitional and comparison content to build or rework, structured data implementation
        (FAQPage, Organization, and Article schema where relevant), and ongoing measurement of where and how your
        brand shows up across AI platforms over time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <FaqAccordion items={faqs} />

    <RelatedLinks
      links={[
        {
          label: 'Work With Me',
          href: '/packages',
          description: 'See how AEO fits into a full engagement.',
        },
        {
          label: 'About',
          href: '/about',
          description: 'The journalism background behind the strategy.',
        },
        {
          label: 'Content Systems',
          href: '/services/content-systems',
          description: 'The content infrastructure AEO depends on.',
        },
      ]}
    />

    <CtaBanner
      heading="Want to know where your brand stands today?"
      body="We'll show you exactly where you're visible — and invisible — across AI search and traditional search."
    />
  </div>
</Layout>
